       All  function arguments are passed by value.  The value of
       a statement that is an expression is  printed  unless  the
       main operator is an assignment.  Either semicolons or new-
       lines may separate statements.  Assignment to scale influ-
       ences  the  number  of digits to be retained on arithmetic
       operations in the manner of dc.  Assignments to  ibase  or
       obase  set the input and output number radix respectively.

       The same letter may be used as an array, a function, and a
       simple  variable simultaneously.  All variables are global
       to the program.  auto variables  are  pushed  down  during
       function  calls.   When using arrays as function arguments
       or defining them  as  automatic  variables,  empty  square
       brackets must follow the array name.

