       The bc command does not recognize the logical operators &&
       and ||.

       The for statement must have all three expressions (E's).

       The quit statement is interpreted when read, not when exe-
       cuted.

       For certain operations, the value of scale might be calcu-
       lated to be larger than the current specified scale value.
       When  you  set  scale  to  a  large  value, take this into
       account when performing operations that could overflow the
       specified scale value.

